HEADWORD: Discriminative
<hw>Dis*crim"i*na*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Marking a difference; distinguishing; distinctive;
characteristic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That peculiar and <qex>discriminative</qex> form of life.</q>
<rj><qau>Johnson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Observing distinctions; making differences;
discriminating.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Discriminative</xex> censure.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>J. Foster.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Discriminative</xex> Providence.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dr. H. More.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discriminatively</ent>⟦br⟧
